```kotlin
object Constants {
 const val IMAGE_BASE_URL = "https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/"

 // Common image sizes from TMDB
 const val SIZE_W200 = "w200"
 const val SIZE_W500 = "w500"
 const val SIZE_W780 = "w780"
}
```

You can now build URLs like:

```kotlin
posterImage.load("${Constants.IMAGE_BASE_URL}${Constants.SIZE_W500}${movie.poster_path}")
```

Next steps you may want to consider (if youâ€™d like me to implement them, let me know):

1. Replace every hard-coded `"w200"`, `"w500"`, and `"w780"` with the corresponding constants.
